What is your overall assessment of this course?
Do you expect to use this class for credit toward your major, or toward a pre-professional program?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Well, you have to take it anyways if you're a senior in the major. The earlier you get this stuff done, the more at ease you'll be toward deadlines. Class doesn't meet much towards the middle of the semester; it feels like you aren't even taking a class until, oops, you have 20 pages due some Wednesday. Student presentations at the end are a cool opportunity to see what other students in the major are working on.
EVST 496 is required for the major but worth taking to a certain extent.
Again, required. Why you looking up evaluations?
